snippet.textDisplay: As a Nuggets fan I would hardly take anything from this game. Lebron is a beast. Honestly Lakers right now have nothing to worry about and those people saying Lakers suck, well you all are just speculating, they got the best record in the west so far, and the rest is all to be seen. Lebron is still playing out of his mind and the Lakers could beat any team at any given moment, but so could the Nuggets, Bucks, Sixers, Clippers and a few others out there. I think its great to have all this uncertainty, it just makes the league so much more exciting. I was a bit annoyed Lebron wasn't playing because he is kind of a test on how strong the Lakers are... basically him and AD. We lost the last one so not gonna get too excited about this win. On to the next one. Good game and hopefully Bron will play in the next game against us, we wanna know how to contain him and its hard to do that if he doesn't play regular season games.
